<br>
Time goes by, I get my sister in this game. She makes a Human Paladin of Karana. Even more time goes by, I see her getting her guild together to take out Lucan at level 39. The same guild had a Mistmoore raid a month ago and she had her hilt. She had everything good to go, the faction, the items, all that was needed was Lucan's testimony.<br>
<br>
Then she gets a group together to rampage through Paw to get to Brother Hayle. She then recieves her SoulFire, everyone cheers, I congratulate my sister on how far shes gotten since she was that level 3 naked newbie slashing Fire Beetles in Qeynos with a Rusty Scythe.<br>
<br>
Even more time passes by, I start on Sullon Zek server as a paladin. I guess you can call it kind of a Pally tradition, hehe. Currently im only level 15 and I have a long way to go, but still, I look forward to starting this epic quest. Not the Firey Defender epic mind you, but the quest itself feels epic, the ultimate battle against the forces of evil and corruption. Even so, the quest will be much more difficult, as one team controls Mistmoore and another controls Freeport. But I still want to do this quest because of the challenge and for Paladin status.<br>
<br>
I dunno how I got to writing this post hehe. But it is depressing to see SoulFire down to practically nothing, worse even than a RunnyEye weapon. Still though, it would be great if Verant upgraded it somehow. Here are a few suggestions.<br>
<br>
1. Add a quest to recharge SoulFire. And at the same time only allow those charges to be used when its wielded. I know this isnt my idea, but I still think its great.<br>
<br>
2. Maybe add an alternate quest to upgrade SoulFire. Perhaps Valeron Dushire wants to check on the spy they have hidden in Neriak and he wants you to bring back information that he is carrying. You get through Neriak to the Knight of Truth spy and give him a note. He gives you a note with information about Dark Elves infiltrating their ranks. Then a Dark Elf Necromancer NPC will spawn and your group has to kill him. Shouldnt be increadibly tough, but challenging. Sneaking through Neriak would be a real hard part and so will the NPC.<br>
<br>
Then you bring back the heart of the Dark Elf and the note the spy gave you to Valeron. This triggers 3 Dark Elf spies to spawn, possibly in the same area that the Freeport Militia spy spawned. This should be a pretty challenging fight as well, maybe even Lucan sized. Once you kill them, bring thier helms along with your SoulFire to Valeron and he gives you the upgraded SoulFire, possibly with more Damage, more Strength and Wisdom bonuses, more charges of Complete Heal, and maybe even some resists.<br>
<br>
3. Also like everyone said, add the Bash to the sword, plus the Bane damage and the Elemental damage.<br>
<br>
Those are my thoughts and a little history as to what I see the SoulFire blade as.<br>
<br>
Crint, 15th season Dwarven Paladin<br>
